 research design, providing a new framework to link theory and empirics. Drawing on diverse examples from political science, it presents a typology of the rich set of interactions that are possible between theory and empirics. This typology opens up new ways for scholars to make progress on substantive questions, and enables researchers from disparate traditions to gain a deeper appreciation for each other's work and why it matters.Theory and Credibility shows theorists how to create models that are genuinely useful to empirical inquiry, and helps empiricists better understand how to structure their research in ways that speak to theoretically meaningful questions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEmpiricism. 0aMathematical models. 0aQuantitative research. 0aSocial sciencesxResearchxPhilosophy. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aA Model Discipline.  aDavid M. Primo.  aElements of Research Design.  aKevin A. Clarke.  aMethods and Models.  aNatural Experiments in the Social Sciences.  aRebecca B. Morton.  aThad Dunning.  aall-else-equal relationships.  adisentangling.  adistinguishing.  aelaborating.  aempirical analysis.  aexternal validity.  aextrapolation.  agame theory.  aincrementalism.  aintentional explanations.  aportability.  aquantitative methods.  areinterpretation.  areinterpreting.  arobustness.  asimilarityall-else-equal claims.  asocial phenomena.  atransparency.1 aBerry, Christopher R., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBueno de Mesquita, Ethan, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTit